    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Adhesive and binding material that is a preparation of refined asphalt and heavy petroleum oil, made by refining petroleum until there is no water or foreign matter in it, except for the minerals naturally found in the asphalt. Asphalt cement contains less than one percent ash. Usually used for paving.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
